-- China Gold Investment Demand May Gain to 150 Tons This Year, Council Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-02T04:12:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-02/china-gold-investment-demand-may-gain-to-150-tons-this-year-council-says.html
China’s investment gold demand may
reach 150 metric tons this year, up from 105 tons last year,
Albert Cheng, managing director of the World Gold Council’s Far
East department, told a conference in Shanghai today. That’s an
even larger increase when compared with the 3-4 tons 10 years
ago, Cheng said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
